.TH HADAL 1 "2026-02-25" "hadal 0.1.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
hadal \- audiophile-grade terminal music player for Linux
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B hadal
[\fIOPTIONS\fR] [\fIPATH\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B Hadal
is a terminal-based music player designed for audiophile-quality playback.
It supports FLAC, MP3, AAC, Ogg Vorbis, Opus, WAV, AIFF, and ALAC formats.
Features include a 10-band parametric equalizer, real-time spectrum analyzer
and VU meters, album art via the Kitty image protocol, and a ranger-style
library browser.
.PP
Named after the hadal zone \(em the deepest oceanic trenches \(em where only
the purest signals reach.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-c, \-\-config \fIFILE\fR
Path to configuration file. Defaults to
.IR ~/.config/hadal/config.toml .
.TP
.B \-d, \-\-debug
Enable debug logging to
.IR ~/.cache/hadal/hadal.log .
.TP
.B \-\-scan
Force library scan on startup.
.TP
.B \-\-list\-devices
List available audio output devices and exit.
.TP
.B \-\-version\-info
Print detailed version and build information.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I ~/.config/hadal/config.toml
Main configuration file.
.TP
.I ~/.config/hadal/keybindings.toml
Custom keybinding overrides.
.TP
.I ~/.local/share/hadal/library.db
Music library SQLite database.
.TP
.I ~/.local/share/hadal/eq_state.toml
Persisted equalizer state.
.TP
.I ~/.local/share/hadal/playlists.db
Playlist database.
.TP
.I ~/.cache/hadal/hadal.log
Application log file.
